summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, 
Endorses the understanding that UNIFIL will deploy and function fully throughout its area of operations and the Government of Lebanon will strengthen its presence; 
Extends UNIFIL's mandate for 6 months, until 31 January 2001; 
Supports Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and political independence; 
Welcomes Israel's removal of all violations of the withdrawal line; 
Calls on parties to respect the line, exercise restraint and cooperate with the UN and UNIFIL; 
Urges the Government of Lebanon to ensure its effective authority in the south, including through deployment of Lebanese armed forces; 
Welcomes establishment of checkpoints by Lebanon and encourages a calm environment; 
Re-emphasizes UNIFIL's terms of reference; 
Requests the Secretary-General to continue consultations and report to the Council; 
Looks forward to early fulfilment of UNIFIL's mandate; 
Welcomes the Secretary-General's intention to report on progress towards achieving objectives; 
Decides to review the situation in early November 2000; 
Stresses the importance of a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East.
